notes: Solo. Climbed the ice gully in grater rock
Solo up, rapped through the crux on the way down. Super fun, but definitely a bit scary

Lead P1, Adam rope gunned the rest. 2:30am start from TH, topped the route at noon and back at the car around 5:45pm. Climbing north chimney was really really cold but everything else after that was mostly tolerable even once it went into the shade. No barfies. Really fun quality climbing on every pitch, but fuck the squeeze chimney on P4, it felt harder than the one on P7 imo. Got snowed on pretty good during the crux pitch, enough to make the final traverse pitch very wet and pretty scary. Due
Bailed below peewee tower. Too cold. Ice and snow on at least half of the route

/ Onsight. Lead P1, P2, P5.5 to the summit. Mixture of simul + pitching out. Got off route twice onto 5.8 territory. Ironically the off route bits were the best pitches. Overall I'd say this route is over hyped just like Whitney is for hiking. It's completely fine but there are far betters out there

P1 only. Hit sunset at the crows nest. Beautiful from there looking at hop scotch. Anchor was the blue dmm, yellow offset, red tricam. The red tricam was fucking bomber, passive mode set. Blue cam not so great
/ Onsight. Only climbed P1, set an anchor on a small tree, not ideal. Set up for Bennett to TR, Kevin led. Rap to descend from slung ring
ed pretty much everything above el cap spire. Led 11d bolts from Long Ledge at sunset. Wowie!
Climbed to the Block in 14 hours with miles. (Pitch 21 or 24 depending on topo) Then we rapped. Gotta go back a bit fitter for the Siad

/ Onsight. In a day with Will! Pretty epic and cool to feel my body working well again. Brought the wrong size shoes (full size too small) which was tough and got pretty dehydrated on my block. Lead from hollow flake to below enduros. First time on route for me except for P1 of freeblast
Followed as dry route. Didnâ€™t finish last two pitches. Was a hybrid route of adjacent lines
Follow p3, lead p4 with mark. Adventure climbing, little bit of groveling owish things
Followed first pitch, did toe crack, lead 3rd and 5th pitch
